      "note_no": "43",
      "note": "The verb 'alima, which primarily denotes \"he knew\", has also the meaning of \"he came to know\", i.e., \"he understood\"; and since - as pointed out by Baghawi, Zamakhshari and Razi - the pronoun \"they\" in the phrase law kanu ya'lamun relates to the deniers of the truth spoken of in the preceding passages, the rendering \"if they could but understand\" is here clearly indicated - the more so as it provides a self-evident connection with the subsequent, objective clause."
